Rider, who was raced with 210 km/h, and hot drinks between the legs, receives £1,000 penalty
A car driver was a penalty of £1,000 imposed because he was hit with up to 210 km/h and a hot drink between his legs.
Andrew Howie, 35, from Tiptree, Essex, was stopped on May 27 with his Mercedes Benz on the A120 to Braintree.
After the police had stopped him, they discovered the Cup between his legs.
Before the District Court of Colchester Howie pled guilty, without being the necessary care and attention.
He received seven points and a six-month driving ban.
Howie was in addition to the payment of costs amounting to £90 and a victim surcharge of £100 sentenced.
